The new Director-General, Nigerian Civil Aviation Authority (NCAA), Capt. Musa Shuaibu Nuhu, on Monday assumed duties as chief executive of the regulatory body. The brief handover, which was superintended by the Acting Director-General, Capt. Sidi Abdullahi, held at the Conference Room, Aviation House, Ikeja. He resumed as the seventh DG of the authority,Â  following his appointment on October 23, last year and confirmation by the Senate. Capt Abdullahi urged staff members to support the new helmsman to take the authority to greater heights.